\subsection{Whole Brain MHSA in vbjax}

vbjax implements a Cortico-Thalamic Multi-Head Self-Attention (CT-MHSA) model that combines structural brain connectivity with differentiable attention mechanisms. The model operates across $N=84$ brain regions with $H=8$ attention heads, each using key/value dimension $D_k=D_v=16$. At each timestep, input features $x_t \in \mathbb{R}^{B \times N \times D_{model}}$ are projected to queries, keys, and values via learnable matrices $W_Q, W_K, W_V$. The memory matrix $M_t \in \mathbb{R}^{B \times N \times H \times D_v \times D_k}$ is updated using the Delta Rule: $M_t = M_{t-1} + \lambda(v_t k_t^T - M_{t-1})$, where $\lambda=0.9$ is a forgetting factor. Output is retrieved via $o_t = M_t q_t$ and aggregated across heads with $W_Y$. Region-to-region coupling is governed by a structural connectivity matrix $C \in \mathbb{R}^{N \times N}$, enabling delayed signal propagation based on tract lengths. The entire sequence is computed efficiently using \texttt{jax.lax.scan}.